# Neon Migration Delivery Rules

## Intent
Ensure every database schema/data change in the rewrite is reflected in `ctf/schema.sql`, which is the canonical schema for Neon.

## Mandatory
- Any change that affects database schema, constraints, indexes, or data transformations must be made directly in `ctf/schema.sql`.

## Delivery Requirements
- PR description must include a `Migration` section when DB changes are present, referencing the relevant changes in `ctf/schema.sql` and a rollback strategy (or explicit note when not safely reversible).
- If no DB change is made, PR should state `Migration: none`.

## SQL Safety Rules
- Prefer additive changes first (new columns/tables/indexes), then backfill, then enforcement.
- Avoid destructive operations without explicit backup/rollback notes.
- Include transactional boundaries where supported.
- Use idempotent guards where practical (`IF EXISTS`, `IF NOT EXISTS`).

## Prohibited
- Shipping DB-impacting code without updating `ctf/schema.sql`.
- Requiring manual guesswork to execute schema changes.
- Bundling unrelated schema changes in one commit without rationale.
